      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">Achieving the vision of 'smart manufacturing' and 'Industrie 4.0'
                requires building on successes in computational control of processes to create
                generic approaches for management of manufacturing operations, or smart
                manufacturing operations management (SMOM). The approach to SMOM presented in this
                report generalizes the modeling framework of ISA-95 with a reference model for
                discrete event logistics systems (DELS) that identifes fve generic operations
                management decisions. This report applies it in a computational model of a
                large-scale, highly-automated central fll pharmacy that is the basis for a
                simulation testbed enabling convenient experimentation with operations management
                policies and decision algorithms.</abstract>
